@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor #ffffff
skinparam DefaultFontName Sora
skinparam DefaultFontColor #1a1a1a
skinparam DefaultFontSize 13
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam padding 5
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #d96a1f
    ArrowFontColor #1a1a1a
    LifeLineBorderColor #9a9a9a
    LifeLineBackgroundColor #ffffff

    ParticipantBorderColor #d96a1f
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #fff4ec
    ParticipantFontColor #1a1a1a

    ActorBorderColor #d96a1f
    ActorBackgroundColor #fff4ec
    ActorFontColor #1a1a1a

    BoxBorderColor #cccccc
    BoxBackgroundColor #f7f7f7
    BoxFontColor #1a1a1a

    GroupHeaderFontColor #ffffff
    GroupBackgroundColor #d96a1f
    GroupBorderColor #d96a1f
    GroupFontColor #ffffff
    GroupBodyBackgroundColor #fafafa

    DividerBackgroundColor #fff4ec
    DividerBorderColor #d96a1f
    DividerFontColor #d96a1f
}

skinparam note {
    BorderColor #d96a1f
    BackgroundColor #fff9f3
    FontColor #3a3a3a
}

skinparam database {
    BorderColor #d96a1f
    BackgroundColor #fff4ec
    FontColor #1a1a1a
}

actor "Developer" as dev
box "Copilot (Haiku)" #fff4ec
  participant "Orchestrator" as copilot
end box
box "7 Researchers (Haiku, read-only)" #f7f7f7
  participant "R1: Jira" as r1
  participant "R2: Slack" as r2
  participant "R3: GitHub" as r3
  participant "R4: Confluence" as r4
  participant "R5: Backend" as r5
  participant "R6: Frontend" as r6
  participant "R7: Datadog" as r7
end box
database "ChromaDB" as chroma

== Phase 0: Scope (Copilot, Haiku) ==

dev -> copilot : "investiga EXP-3580"
copilot -> r1 : Read Jira ticket
r1 --> copilot : Refund $45.20 instead of $50.00

== Phase 0.5: Service Chain (Copilot, Haiku) ==

copilot -> chroma : query_vault("refund FX rounding")
chroma --> copilot : Pitfall: "promoAmount must\nbe propagated, not recalculated"
copilot -> copilot : Map service chain:\ncustomer -> svc-order -> svc-experiences -> provider

== Phase 1: Evidence Sweep (7 Researchers, Haiku, parallel) ==

copilot -> r1 : Jira: related tickets
copilot -> r2 : Slack: error reports, workarounds
copilot -> r3 : GitHub: recent PRs, blame, releases
copilot -> r4 : Confluence: ADRs, runbooks
copilot -> r5 : Backend: grep svc-order refund.ts
copilot -> r6 : Frontend: admin refund UI
copilot -> r7 : Datadog: logs, traces, metrics

note over r1, r7 : **All 7 run simultaneously**\n~3-5 min total (vs 2-4h manual)

r1 --> copilot : EXP-3201: similar bug 3mo ago
r2 --> copilot : 3 CS reports this week
r3 --> copilot : PR #4521 changed refund.ts\nMath.round -> Math.floor
r4 --> copilot : ADR: "propagate, never recalculate"
r5 --> copilot : FX applied when currencies match\n(should be skipped)
r6 --> copilot : Admin UI sends correct currency
r7 --> copilot : Spike started 14 days ago\n(matches PR #4521 merge)

== Phase 2: Synthesis (Copilot, Haiku) ==

copilot -> copilot : Cross-reference 7 sources\nReconstruct timeline\n5 Whys root cause analysis

note right of copilot
  **Root cause**: PR #4521 removed
  currency check condition.
  FX now applies to same-currency
  refunds. Confirmed by GitHub
  diff + Datadog traces.
  **Impact**: ~47 refunds affected.
end note

== Phase 3: Fix Plan (Copilot, Haiku) ==

copilot --> dev : **2 approaches with trade-offs**\nA: Restore currency check (recommended)\nB: FX rate 1.0 for same-currency

== Phase 4: Document (Copilot, Haiku) ==

copilot -> chroma : Save Investigation-Case.md\n(auto-indexed in ~30s)

note over chroma : Next time someone touches\nrefund.ts, query_vault returns:\n"FX only when currencies differ.\nSee EXP-3580."

@enduml
